   <P style="float: left;padding: 10px 15px;width: 98%;text-align: justify;"> The curriculum of the Programme is designed to expose the candidates to foundations of business management and deep skills in analytics. The curriculum entails exhaustive coverage of academic concepts blended with rich industry exposure and hands on training on the requisite skills and technologies needed for the Analytics sector.</p>
</div>
<div class="underlinetext">
   <P style="float: left;padding: 10px 15px;width: 98%;text-align: justify;">The courses are a judicious mix of domain knowledge, quantitative subjects, technical skills and applications. The first few modules of the Programme will focus on the domain competency along with exposure to rigors of the analytical tools and techniques. Subsequently, the participants will be given expertise in handling large data sets in terms of processing, managing, analyzing and representing them in a format that makes Business decisions easy. The latter portion of the curriculum focuses on specific problems encountered in domains such as Finance, marketing, Web, Health, Energy, Telecom etc, and candidates will learn the Business Analytics approaches to solve these problems. </p>
</div>
<div class="underlinetext">
   <P style="float: left;padding: 10px 15px;width: 98%;text-align: justify;">Hands on exposure: Every module will entail practical assignments that complement the conceptual learning that the candidates would have gathered. These assignments will expose the candidates to solving real world business problems using tools such as SAS, R, Tableau, etc.</p>
