 <div class="tab-pane" id="faq" style="padding:20px;">
<div class="underlinetext">
  <h2>FAQ's</h2>
       <div id="faqs">
          <div id="question" align="left">
              <i class="icon-question-sign icon"></i>
              <span><b>What is the eligibility criteria for this programme?</b></span>
          </div>
          <div id="answer" align="left">
              <span>The Post Graduate Programme in Business Analytics (PGP-BA) is an Analytics focused management programme designed and delivered by Great Lakes Institute of Management. Since this is an executive programme that prepares professionals for managerial careers in Analytics, a prior work experience of at least two years is required. However, there is no upper limit on the amount of prior work experience. </span>
          </div>
           <div id="question" align="left">
              <i class="icon-question-sign icon"></i>
              <span><b>What is the programme architecture for PGP-BA?</b></span>
          </div>
          <div id="answer" align="left">
              <span>The programme duration will be for 11 months wherein the candidates would attend classes for 5 days (Friday-Tuesday) every alternate month at Great Lakes Gurgaon campus, with the remaining sessions being available online. In terms of hours, the classroom sessions across 11 months would amount to 240 hours and the online learning material would be for an other 250 hours.   
</span>
          </div>
           <div id="question" align="left">
              <i class="icon-question-sign icon"></i>
              <span><b>What is the programme calendar for PGP-BA?
</b></span>
          </div>
          <div id="answer" align="left">
              <span>The Post Graduate Programme in Business Analytics commences in November 2013 and the class shall graduate in September 2014. The six classroom contact session shall happen in the months of November'13, January'14, March'14, May'14, July'14 and September'14. The intervening months shall have online sessions for the candidates to practise, apply and pace their self learning.
</span>
          </div>
           <div id="question" align="left">
              <i class="icon-question-sign icon"></i>
              <span><b>What is unique about the curriculum in PGP-BA?
</b></span>
          </div>
          <div id="answer" align="left">
              <span>PGP-BA is unique in curriculum design on the following fronts:<br>
:: The curriculum covers general management subjects and provides a detailed study in analytics <br>
:: The courses are taught by eminent faculty from Great Lakes and senior executives from the analytics industry <br>
:: The programme provides the candidates with hands on exposure to tools such as SAS, Tableau and actual industry case studies through virtual labs, assignments and project <br>
:: The blended delivery model (classroom and online) of the programme makes it convenient for working professionals to attend classroom sessions without having to quit their jobs and also, pace their learning through online sessions. </span>
          </div>
           <div id="question" align="left">
              <i class="icon-question-sign icon"></i>
              <span><b>How will PGP-BA help me progress in my career?
</b></span>
          </div>
          <div id="answer" align="left">
              <span>The Post Graduate Programme in Business Analytics (PGP-BA) equips you with the relevant knowledge and skills to pursue managerial careers with best of analytics companies or move the analytics roles within your existing organisation.
</span>
          </div>
           <div id="question" align="left">
              <i class="icon-question-sign icon"></i>
              <span><b>Is PGP-BA a completely online programme?
</b></span>
          </div>
          <div id="answer" align="left">
              <span>PGP-BA follows a blended learning model wherein classes are conducted at Great Lakes Gurgaon campus and also through an online learning management system.</span>
          </div>
           <div id="question" align="left">
              <i class="icon-question-sign icon"></i>
              <span><b> Will the programme certificates be awarded by Great Lakes?
</b></span>
          </div>
          <div id="answer" align="left">
              <span>The certificates for Post Graduate Programme in Business Analytics would be awarded by Great Lakes Institute of Management.
</span>
          </div>
           <div id="question" align="left">
              <i class="icon-question-sign icon"></i>
              <span><b>Would Great Lakes faculty be teaching in this course?
</b></span>
          </div>
          <div id="answer" align="left">
              <span>The academic modules would be taught be senior faculty from Great Lakes. In addition to to Great Lakes faculty, senior leadership from the industry would also participate in delivering certain topics/modules

</span>
          </div>
           <div id="question" align="left">
              <i class="icon-question-sign icon"></i>
              <span><b>Where will the classes be held?
</b></span>
          </div>
          <div id="answer" align="left">
              <span>The classes during the contact sessions would be conducted at Great Lakes Gurgaon campus
</span>
          </div>
           <div id="question" align="left">
              <i class="icon-question-sign icon"></i>
              <span><b>Is PGP-BA accredited by UGC or AICTE?
</b></span>
          </div>
          <div id="answer" align="left">
              <span>The format of the programme does not lend itself to accreditation from AICTE/UGC. However, Great Lakes is an AICTE accredited institution and is one of the few colleges in India to receive accreditation from AACSB. 
</span>
          </div>
           <div id="question" align="left">
              <i class="icon-question-sign icon"></i>
              <span><b>How can I get more information on the programme?
</b></span>
          </div>
          <div id="answer" align="left">
              <span>For more information on the programme or any kind of assistance, you can contact the admissions team at 0124-4934024 or 9650062121. Alternatively, you can also write to us at <a href="mailto:pgpba@beaconlearning.in" target="_top" style="color:#63a7c9;">pgpba@beaconlearning.in</a></span>
          </div>
           <div id="question" align="left">
              <i class="icon-question-sign icon"></i>
              <span><b>What is the fee payment schedule for the programme?
</b></span>
          </div>
          <div id="answer" align="left">
              <span>The total programme fee of Rs 3 lacs is inclusive of service tax and can be paid at one go or within the following payment schedule:
a. Payment of Rs 50,000 at the time of acceptance of admission
b. Payment of Rs 50,000 before commencement of programme
c. Payment of Rs 100,000 before Dec 31st 2013
d. Payment of Rs 100,000 before Jan 31st 2014</span>
          </div>
           <div id="question" align="left">
              <i class="icon-question-sign icon"></i>
              <span><b>What is the refund policy for the programme?
</b></span>
          </div>
          <div id="answer" align="left">
              <span>Once an offer has been accepted and the fee has been paid, there shall be no refunds.
</span>
          </div>
           <div id="question" align="left">
              <i class="icon-question-sign icon"></i>
              <span><b>Is accommodation also provided?</b></span>
          </div>
          <div id="answer" align="left">
              <span>Accommodation has not been included in the programme fee and can be provided at an additional cost
</span>
          </div>
           <div id="question" align="left">
              <i class="icon-question-sign icon"></i>
              <span><b>Would I have to spend extra on books, online learning material or license fee?</b></span>
          </div>
          <div id="answer" align="left">
              <span>The cost of all requisite learning material, whether in print or online, has been covered in the programme fee </span>
          </div>
           <div id="question" align="left">
              <i class="icon-question-sign icon"></i>
              <span><b>Would the content be available to me after completion of the course?</b></span>
          </div>
          <div id="answer" align="left">
              <span>We believe that learning should continue and hence, all the learning material in terms of lectures and reading content would be available to the candidates post completion of programme.</span>
          </div>
           <div id="question" align="left">
              <i class="icon-question-sign icon"></i>
              <span><b>How will I be evaluated during the programme?</b></span>
          </div>
          <div id="answer" align="left">
              <span>PGP-BA is designed to be a holistic and rigorous programme and follows a continuos evaluation. Every contact session would have evaluation examination in addition to the assignments and project work, which are also evaluated.</span>
          </div>
           <div id="question" align="left">
              <i class="icon-question-sign icon"></i>
              <span><b>Can my company sponsor me?</b></span>
          </div>
          <div id="answer" align="left">
              <span>We accept corporate sponsorships and can assist you with the process. For more information, you can write to us at <a href="mailto:pgpba@beaconlearning.in" target="_top" style="color:#63a7c9;">pgpba@beaconlearning.in</a></span>
          </div>
           <div id="question" align="left">
              <i class="icon-question-sign icon"></i>
              <span><b>Will there be placements at the completion of the programme?</b></span>
          </div>
          <div id="answer" align="left">
              <span>Placement services are not a part of this programme. However, having acquired the relevant skills and knowledge most wanted by the analytics industry, are best trained to secure jobs with the best of analytics companies or growth within their existing organisations.</span>
          </div>
           <div id="question" align="left">
              <i class="icon-question-sign icon"></i>
              <span><b>What is the admission process?</b></span>
          </div>
          <div id="answer" align="left">
              <span>  All interested candidates are required to apply to the programme through the online application form. A panel of Great Lakes faculty evaluates all applications and therein, the shortlisted candidates are contacted for interviews. The interviews may be conducted in person or through telephonic or video conferencing. 

</span>
          </div>
           <div id="question" align="left">
              <i class="icon-question-sign icon"></i>
              <span><b>How can I apply for the programme?</b></span>
          </div>
          <div id="answer" align="left">
              <span>If you are interested in the programme, you can apply through the online application form. If you need assistance from our team, write to us at <a href="mailto:pgpba@beaconlearning.in" target="_top" style="color:#63a7c9;">pgpba@beaconlearning.in </a>or call us at 0124-4934024 / 9650062121 and we shall guide you through the process.</span>
          </div>
</div>
</div></div>
</div>
